        <mxCell id="e9IcfTrFGZrHft3Bkj_m-1" value="&lt;h1 style=&quot;margin-top: 0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 18px;&quot;&gt;SQ&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 18px;&quot;&gt;Planning Manager&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 18px;&quot;&gt;1.&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;Does the 45-minute rolling planning horizon provide sufficient foresight to prevent bottlenecks, or does this &quot;short-sightedness&quot; lead to suboptimal outcomes?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 18px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;2.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;Is the planning algorithm fast enough to recalculate in real-time when disturbances occur? (&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;math-inline&quot; data-math=&quot;CalculationTime&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;124&quot; style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); font-family: &amp;quot;Google Sans Text&amp;quot;, sans-serif !important; line-height: 1.15 !important; margin-top: 0px !important;&quot;&gt;CalculationTime&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;vs. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;math-inline&quot; data-math=&quot;UpdateInterval&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;144&quot; style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); font-family: &amp;quot;Google Sans Text&amp;quot;, sans-serif !important; line-height: 1.15 !important; margin-top: 0px !important;&quot;&gt;UpdateInterval&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 18px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;3.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;Are low-priority tasks systematically pushed back, leading to disproportionately long waiting times?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 18px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 18px;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Business Manager&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 18px;&quot;&gt;4.What is the discrepancy between the theoretically calculated capacity (best case without congestion) and the simulated reality?&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 18px;&quot;&gt;5.&amp;nbsp; How stable is the achieved delivery capacity across multiple simulation runs under identical conditions?&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 18px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 18px;&quot;&gt;Order Manager&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 18px;&quot;&gt;6.&amp;nbsp; How reliable is the planner’s prediction regarding the &quot;feasibility&quot; of delivery promises?&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;overflow=hidden;rounded=0;" parent="1" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="80.98" y="960" width="1400" height="520" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
      </root>
    </mxGraphModel>
  </diagram>
